[226.718361, "o", "\r\nв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓ\r\n  ACT 4: Critical Review\r\n"]
[226.718522, "o", "в”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓ\r\n\r\n"]
[261.066782, "o", "Here are the findings:\r\n\r\n## Errors\r\n\r\n- **`package.json` missing `bin` field.** TD-001 specifies `\"bin\": { \"convert\": \"./bin/convert.js\" }` and the PRD says the entry point is `bin/convert`. The actual `package.json` has no `bin` field, so `npx convert` / `npm link` won't work as documented.\r\n\r\n## Omissions\r\n\r\n- **No negative-temperature test.** Both specs mention `-40.0` as an example output (PRD F3). The unique property that в€’40 В°F = в€’40 В°C is an obvious edge case, but no test covers negative inputs.\r\n- **No test for `toFahrenheit` beyond a single value.** `toFahrenheit` has one test (0 в†’ 32); `toCelsius` has two. Parity is missing (e.g., 100 в†’ 212).\r\n- **No CLI-level tests.** TD-001 specifies argument parsing, NaN validation, stderr output, and exit code 1 on error. None of this is tested вЂ” only the pure functions are exercised.\r\n- **No test for the error/missing-flag path.** The TD defines exit code 1 for invalid or missing arguments; this behaviour is untested.\r\n- **User story acceptance criteria are thin.** US-001 lists only two examples (212в†’100, 0в†’32). It doesn't cover: negative temps, fractional inputs, error handling, or the formatting requirement (F3). These are all specified in the PRD and TD but not traceable through the user story.\r\n\r\n## Mischaracterizations / Inconsistencies\r\n\r\n- **PRD entry point vs. actual file.** PRD says `bin/convert` (no extension); the actual file is `bin/convert.js`. This is minor вЂ” the shebang makes it runnable without the extension вЂ” but without the `bin` field in `package.json`, the documented `convert` command name is never registered.\r\n- **TD says \"Guard clause runs only when file is executed directly\" (D3)** вЂ” this is correctly implemented via `require.main === module`, but the TD doesn't note that this pattern won't work under ES modules. Not a bug today, but the constraint is implicit.\r\n\r\n## What's Correct\r\n\r\n- Conversion formulas in `bin/convert.js` match the PRD and TD exactly.\r\n- Output formatting (`toFixed(1)`) matches PRD F3.\r\n- The two acceptance criteria in US-001 (212в†’100.0, 0в†’32.0) are directly covered by existing tests.\r\n- Error handling logic (NaN check, missing flag) matches the TD spec.\r\n- Zero external dependencies constraint is met.\r\n"]
[266.069648, "o", "\r\nв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓ\r\n  ACT 5: Queue Health & Triage\r\nв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓ\r\n\r\n"]
[281.267211, "o", "1. No test for `--to-celsius` CLI flag with valid input (stderr/stdout/exit code)\r\n2. No test for `--to-fahrenheit` CLI flag with valid input (stderr/stdout/exit code)\r\n3. No test for missing flag error (`Error: missing --to-celsius or --to-fahrenheit flag`, exit 1)\r\n4. No test for invalid value after `--to-celsius` (`Error: invalid temperature value`, exit 1)\r\n5. No test for invalid value after `--to-fahrenheit` (`Error: invalid temperature value`, exit 1)\r\n6. No test for missing value after flag (e.g. `--to-celsius` with no following arg вЂ” `parseFloat(undefined)` в†’ NaN path)\r\n7. No test for `toFahrenheit` with negative input (e.g. в€’40 В°C в†’ в€’40 В°F)\r\n8. No test for `toCelsius` with negative input (e.g. в€’40 В°F в†’ в€’40 В°C)\r\n9. No test for `toFahrenheit` with fractional input (e.g. 36.6 В°C)\r\n10. No test that CLI output is rounded to one decimal place (`.toFixed(1)`)\r\n11. No test for both flags provided simultaneously (undefined behavior вЂ” silently picks `--to-celsius`)\r\n12. No test for non-numeric string as value (e.g. `--to-celsius abc`)\r\n"]
